  "texts": [
    "It can reduce people's perception of uncertainties and risks, and thus increase trust in AI.",
    "The acceptance and utilization of AI are guided by both cognitive judgments and affective responses.",
    "As such, it is crucial for trust research in AI to address both the cognitive and the emotional components (Gursoy et al., 2019).",
    "Specifically, emotional experience has been shown to directly impact the willingness to adopt AI-based recommendation systems, as seen in the context of travel planning (Shi et al., 2020).",
    "Sense of control represents individuals' perception of their ability to monitor and influence AI decision-making processes."
